('en', 'README.md', 'Purpose', 3, array['FitLog_Agent', 'English', 'Purpose']::text[], 'fitlog-agent-english-purpose-d62e63bcfd', 1, 1, '### Purpose

FitLog_Agent is an AI-assisted food and workout logging app. It is for users who want to manage diet, training, and body-weight changes without spending excessive effort looking up food composition, estimating portions, calculating calories/macros, and repeatedly entering records by hand.

Traditional food logging is hard because users need to understand ingredients, calories, and macros; recording is easiest before eating, while portions become harder to estimate after the meal; and a slow workflow is difficult to keep long term. FitLog_Agent reduces that friction: AI can turn text or images into drafts, help decide what to eat next, review recent behavior, and explain app rules. Deterministic algorithms still own targets, macros, workout calories, and strategy boundaries. Official records and goal changes still require user confirmation.

FitLog_Agent inherits deterministic logging and algorithm foundations from FitLog Local, but this README describes FitLog_Agent as its own Agent V1 product: signed-in cloud official records plus an AI Chat entry for user-initiated assistance.', 'Source: README.md > FitLog_Agent > English > Purpose. Status: implemented. Tags: agent, algorithm, privacy, ui. Purpose: answer FitLog product-rule, algorithm, database, privacy-boundary, or Agent-boundary questions.', null, array['agent', 'algorithm', 'privacy', 'ui']::text[], 'implemented', '6ec30a97edf51906f8f3eb15b55fe6935196dd39f4a762683140129d3cc04952', 'phase5_document_chunks.v2', timezone('utc', now())),
('en', 'README.md', 'Product Promise', 3, array['FitLog_Agent', 'English', 'Product Promise']::text[], 'fitlog-agent-english-product-promise-7b3be5d4ad', 1, 1, '### Product Promise

```text
Make logging easier.
Keep deterministic diet and workout rules.
Use AI only for drafts, suggestions, reviews, and explanations.
Require user confirmation for official writes, deletes, and goal changes.
```', 'Source: README.md > FitLog_Agent > English > Product Promise. Status: implemented. Tags: agent, ui. Purpose: answer FitLog product-rule, algorithm, database, privacy-boundary, or Agent-boundary questions.', null, array['agent', 'ui']::text[], 'implemented', 'ac113a9b1103af8bac0e84d19c4dd615169d5c948b4a7bd412958080fb5cbc0c', 'phase5_document_chunks.v2', timezone('utc', now())),
('en', 'README.md', 'Core Capabilities', 3, array['FitLog_Agent', 'English', 'Core Capabilities']::text[], 'fitlog-agent-english-core-capabilities-97fccc3d68', 1, 1, '### Core Capabilities

- Food logging: manual entry, AI Food Analysis, Food Draft preview/edit, copy-to-date, and delete.
- Workout logging: workout drafts, official workout records, custom exercises, and strength/cardio calorie estimates.
- Profile and targets: Cloud Profile, diet phase, `energy_ratio`, `gram_per_kg`, carb cycling, carb tapering, and body metrics.
- AI Chat: centered AI page with text, up to three images, and server-side ChatGPT/OpenAI plus Qwen providers.
- Meal decisions: when users ask what to eat next, AI uses the minimum needed Profile, summary, and context.
- Weekly review: AI can summarize recent food, training, weight trends, and data gaps, but cannot automatically change goals or strategies.
- App logic Q&A: Document RAG explains FitLog algorithms, fields, privacy, and Agent boundaries.
- Export: user-controlled XLSX or CSV ZIP export.', 'Source: README.md > FitLog_Agent > English > Core Capabilities. Status: implemented. Tags: agent, algorithm, methodology, privacy, ui. Purpose: answer FitLog product-rule, algorithm, database, privacy-boundary, or Agent-boundary questions.', null, array['agent', 'algorithm', 'methodology', 'privacy', 'ui']::text[], 'implemented', 'db9faea3752004a1ceb0bbf0c9a45c0aa8e94b68b0611b1994e7507a9461b914', 'phase5_document_chunks.v2', timezone('utc', now())),
('en', 'README.md', 'AI And Data Boundaries', 3, array['FitLog_Agent', 'English', 'AI And Data Boundaries']::text[], 'fitlog-agent-english-ai-and-data-boundaries-7c22481bd8', 1, 1, '### AI And Data Boundaries

- Model API keys are server-managed; users do not provide model keys.
- AI outputs are drafts, suggestions, reviews, or explanations until confirmed.
- AI does not silently write official food, workout, Profile, or goal data.
- AI does not automatically apply carb tapering, delete records, or change diet goals.
- Image requests are limited to three images; original images or base64 payloads are not stored long term by default.
- V1 does not create user-business-data vector databases, long-term embeddings, semantic memory, or GraphRAG.
- V1 is not medical diagnosis, treatment advice, or pediatric treatment guidance.', 'Source: README.md > FitLog_Agent > English > AI And Data Boundaries. Status: implemented. Tags: agent, database, methodology, ui. Purpose: answer FitLog product-rule, algorithm, database, privacy-boundary, or Agent-boundary questions.', null, array['agent', 'database', 'methodology', 'ui']::text[], 'implemented', '3195076af201d2a5797dc3db8029e6c2a50b6a57d872752353fa0652b7d6d318', 'phase5_document_chunks.v2', timezone('utc', now())),
('en', 'README.md', 'Diet And Workout Rules', 3, array['FitLog_Agent', 'English', 'Diet And Workout Rules']::text[], 'fitlog-agent-english-diet-and-workout-rules-882201f859', 1, 1, '### Diet And Workout Rules

FitLog_Agent preserves deterministic algorithms as the source for official targets and summaries.

```text
diet_goal_phase:
  - cutting
  - bulking

diet_calculation_mode:
  - energy_ratio
  - gram_per_kg

diet_plan_strategy:
  - none
  - carb_cycling
  - carb_tapering
```

Key boundaries:

- `diet_goal_phase` is the source of cutting / bulking semantics.
- In `energy_ratio`, kcal target / intake / remaining is primary.
- In `gram_per_kg`, macro grams are primary and kcal is auxiliary.
- `carb_cycling` is a user-configured strategy layer, not AI meal automation.
- `carb_tapering` is a review plus user-confirmation flow, not AI automatic carb reduction.
- Workout calories remain deterministic calculations.', 'Source: README.md > FitLog_Agent > English > Diet And Workout Rules. Status: implemented. Tags: agent, algorithm, methodology, ui. Purpose: answer FitLog product-rule, algorithm, database, privacy-boundary, or Agent-boundary questions.', null, array['agent', 'algorithm', 'methodology', 'ui']::text[], 'implemented', '1061ecd36937753c8c8d86d2804bb86b9213dee84b6ecd9418a360fb25df5820', 'phase5_document_chunks.v2', timezone('utc', now())),
('en', 'README.md', 'Cloud And Local Data', 3, array['FitLog_Agent', 'English', 'Cloud And Local Data']::text[], 'fitlog-agent-english-cloud-and-local-data-ee4bfab0bd', 1, 1, '### Cloud And Local Data

After sign-in, official Profile, body metrics, food, workout, and daily summaries use the cloud as the source of truth. Local SQLite remains partial cache, draft storage, and runtime acceleration. FitLog_Agent uses a single-active-device policy; a newer login takes over the account, and the older device stops official writes on the next cloud interaction.

The full cloud/local authority, cache-first reads, warm cache, write-success rules, failures, conflicts, and repair policy live in [docs/en/CloudLocalDataBoundary.md](docs/en/CloudLocalDataBoundary.md) / [docs/zh/CloudLocalDataBoundary.md](docs/zh/CloudLocalDataBoundary.md).', 'Source: README.md > FitLog_Agent > English > Cloud And Local Data. Status: implemented. Tags: agent, database, privacy, ui. Purpose: answer FitLog product-rule, algorithm, database, privacy-boundary, or Agent-boundary questions.', null, array['agent', 'database', 'privacy', 'ui']::text[], 'implemented', '12d7ed4b8b33eb74c8a4678aae37772a7603c120e1716d8d62e5a77439d63925', 'phase5_document_chunks.v2', timezone('utc', now())),
('en', 'README.md', 'Tech Stack', 3, array['FitLog_Agent', 'English', 'Tech Stack']::text[], 'fitlog-agent-english-tech-stack-a2a942590f', 1, 1, '### Tech Stack

- Flutter + Dart
- SQLite via `sqflite`
- `provider` for app services and UI state
- `shared_preferences` for language, theme, and lightweight local state
- `image_picker` for camera/gallery image selection
- `excel`, `csv`, and `archive` for export
- Supabase Auth, Postgres, Storage, and Edge Functions
- OpenAI / ChatGPT and Qwen server-side providers', 'Source: README.md > FitLog_Agent > English > Tech Stack. Status: evidence. Tags: agent, database, privacy, ui. Purpose: answer FitLog product-rule, algorithm, database, privacy-boundary, or Agent-boundary questions.', null, array['agent', 'database', 'privacy', 'ui']::text[], 'evidence', 'ec49203e028f24d735f38c60f21ae306fae7088fd4e7e369094b737d2ab1ea11', 'phase5_document_chunks.v2', timezone('utc', now())),
('en', 'README.md', 'Quick Start', 3, array['FitLog_Agent', 'English', 'Quick Start']::text[], 'fitlog-agent-english-quick-start-3a431364ff', 1, 1, '### Quick Start

Requirements:

- Flutter 3.x
- Dart 3.x
- Android Studio or VS Code
- Android emulator or physical device

Common commands:

```bash
flutter pub get
flutter run
flutter analyze
flutter test
flutter build apk --debug --split-per-abi
```

Account, Cloud Profile, Cloud Records, and real AI Gateway testing need Supabase configuration:

```bash
flutter run --dart-define=SUPABASE_URL=<url> --dart-define=SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<anon-key>
```

You can also copy `config/supabase.local.json.example` to the uncommitted local file `config/supabase.local.json`, fill in the Supabase URL and anon key, then run:

```bash
flutter run --dart-define-from-file=config/supabase.local.json
flutter build apk --debug --split-per-abi --dart-define-from-file=config/supabase.local.json
```', 'Source: README.md > FitLog_Agent > English > Quick Start. Status: implemented. Tags: agent, database, privacy, ui. Purpose: answer FitLog product-rule, algorithm, database, privacy-boundary, or Agent-boundary questions.', null, array['agent', 'database', 'privacy', 'ui']::text[], 'implemented', '09b3943914ed58fbae6c0aa93655dfef60abeb31df402887182ce57c644170c2', 'phase5_document_chunks.v2', timezone('utc', now())),
